## Problem

The workflow `slim/deploy-with-dmv` is failing because Corepack is not enabled in the Node.js container.

**Failed Job:** https://github.com/ImagingDataCommons/idc-viewers-sandbox-gha-testing/actions/runs/21650492159/job/62413535913

### Error Message
```
error This project's package.json defines "packageManager": "yarn@bun@latest". However the current global version of Yarn is 1.22.22.

Presence of the "packageManager" field indicates that the project is meant to be used with Corepack, a tool included by default with all official Node.js distributions starting from 16.9 and 14.19.

Corepack must currently be enabled by running corepack enable in your terminal. For more information, check out https://yarnpkg.com/corepack.
```

## Root Cause

The `slim` repository's `package.json` defines a `packageManager` field, which requires Corepack to be enabled. The workflow uses a `node:20` container where Corepack is available but not enabled by default.

## Solution

Add a step to enable Corepack before running any `yarn install` commands in the workflow file `.github/workflows/deploy-with-dmv.yml`:

```yaml
- name: Enable Corepack
  run: corepack enable
```

This step should be added after the checkout step and before the "Clone and install SLIM dependencies" step.

## Additional Note

The `packageManager` field value in the `slim` repository appears to be "yarn@bun@latest", which looks incorrect. It should typically be something like "yarn@4.0.2" or "yarn@stable". This may need to be investigated in the slim repository.